@startuml
' Inbound chat reply sequence (OpenClaw auto-reply pipeline)

autonumber
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowThickness 1
  LifeLineBorderColor #999999
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #F9F9F9
  ParticipantBorderColor #666666
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9E6
  NoteBorderColor #D6B656
}

actor User
participant "Web chat client\n(Gateway RPC)" as Client
participant "External channel\n(extension handler)" as Ext
participant "Entry\n(chat.send or extension)" as Entry
participant "dispatchInboundMessage\nsrc/auto-reply/dispatch.ts" as Dispatch
participant "dispatchReplyFromConfig\nsrc/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts" as FromCfg
participant "getReplyFromConfig\nsrc/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.ts" as GetReply
participant "runPreparedReply\nsrc/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.ts" as Prep
participant "runReplyAgent\nsrc/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.ts" as Agent
participant "runEmbeddedPiAgent\nsrc/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run.ts" as Pi
participant "Outbound\n(dispatcher.deliver or routeReply)" as Out

note over User, Out
  Entry split: Web Gateway vs external messaging channel
end note

alt Web Gateway chat
  User -> Client: Send message
  Client -> Entry: RPC chat.send\nsrc/gateway/server-methods/chat.ts
  note right of Entry
    Validate params, permissions, sanitize,
    dedupe, send policy, stop command,
    load session
  end note
else External channel
  User -> Ext: Message on provider
  Ext -> Entry: Build MsgContext\n+ dispatchReplyWithBufferedBlockDispatcher\nsrc/auto-reply/reply/provider-dispatcher.ts
  note right of Entry
    Per-channel routing,
    mention / group gating
  end note
end

Entry -> Dispatch: finalizeInboundContext (if needed)\n+ dispatchReplyFromConfig

note over FromCfg
  Dedupe, resolveReplyRoutingDecision,
  hooks, send / typing policy,
  ACP shortcuts, etc.
end note

FromCfg -> GetReply: Produce reply payload(s)

note over GetReply
  finalizeInboundContext,
  resolveCommandAuthorization,
  initSessionState,
  media / link understanding,
  pre-agent hooks
end note

GetReply -> Prep: Build prompt and queue settings
Prep -> Agent: Run agent turn

note over Agent
  Queue, steer, block streaming,
  typing, tool event coalescing
end note

Agent -> Pi: Embedded Pi inference loop

note over Pi
  Provider / model / auth / fallback,
  tool loop, model API calls
end note

Pi --> Agent: Assistant output / payloads / usage
Agent --> Prep: ReplyPayload or array
Prep --> GetReply: Return
GetReply --> FromCfg: ReplyPayload

note over FromCfg, Out
  Cross-surface routing may use routeReply;
  same surface typically uses dispatcher deliver
end note

FromCfg -> Out: deliver or routeReply\nsrc/auto-reply/reply/route-reply.ts
Out -> User: Final message

note over User, Out
  Policy and extension hooks: dispatchReplyFromConfig,
  getReplyFromConfig; model and tools: Pi
end note

@enduml
